data.title: Enterprise (CVN
data.meta_description: Ship History The world's first nuclear-powered aircraft carrier was commissioned on 25 November 1961 and completed 25 deployments during 51 years of service. Click the links below to access the Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Ships entries for Enterprise, which provide the carrier's history by time period. 1961–1965 | 1966–1970 | 1971–1975 | 1976–1980 | 1981–1985 1986–1990 | 1991–1995 | 1996–2000
